    Page: 110
By: Sextus the Pythagorean
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Illusion=The Consummation of Desire
---
Think that you suffer a great punishment when you obtain the object of
corporeal desire; for the attainment of such objects never satisfies desire.
